            "content": "# Decentralized Twitch (twitch-desent)\n\n## Project Overview\n\nDecentralized streaming platform where **streamers self-host their own servers**. The platform provides either a ready-to-deploy binary (streamer buys domain + VPS, enters data in our installer app like Amnezia, we auto-configure everything) or a managed cloud option (with content moderation — no pirated movies/casinos).\n\n### Key Concept\nEach streamer runs their own Go server (single binary). They can:\n- Add Edge CDN nodes for geo-coverage (e.g., Novosibirsk, St. Petersburg)\n- Host other streamers on their server\n- Register in a Discovery catalog (after moderation) so new viewers can find them\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Video Pipeline\n```\nOBS → RTMP (:1935) → FFmpeg (1080p→720p→480p→360p) → HLS segments (2-4 sec) → HTTP delivery (:443)\n```\n\n### Components (Single Binary)\n- **RTMP Ingest** — accepts OBS stream on port 1935\n- **FFmpeg Transcoder** — multi-quality HLS segmentation\n- **HLS Delivery** — serves `.m3u8` playlists and `.ts` segments via HTTP\n- **WebSocket Chat** — 1 dispatcher goroutine, broadcast to all viewers, rooms per stream\n- **Auth** — JWT-based, middleware on all endpoints\n- **Admin API** — stream settings, CDN node management, user/ban management\n- **SQLite** — local database for users, bans, settings, logs\n\n### External Services (NOT in MVP)\n- **Discovery Service** — cloud catalog of trusted servers (PostgreSQL, moderation)\n- **Edge Nodes** — Go binaries that cache HLS segments from origin server\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Language:** Go 1.23\n- **Database:** SQLite (via `modernc.org/sqlite` — pure Go, no CGO)\n- **HTTP Router:** `net/http` (stdlib, Go 1.22+ routing)\n- **WebSocket:** `nhooyr.io/websocket`\n- **JWT:** `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n- **RTMP:** `github.com/nareix/joy5` or custom RTMP listener\n- **Video:** FFmpeg (external process, managed via `os/exec`)\n- **Config:** Environment variables + YAML config file\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\ntwitch-desent/\n├── cmd/\n│   └── server/\n│       └── main.go              # Entry point, wires everything together\n├── internal/\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   └── config.go            # App configuration (env + yaml)\n│   ├── auth/\n│   │   ├── handler.go           # POST /api/auth/register, POST /api/auth/login\n│   │   ├── jwt.go               # JWT generation & validation\n│   │   ├── middleware.go         # Auth middleware (extracts user from token)\n│   │   └── store.go             # User storage (SQLite-backed)\n│   ├── chat/\n│   │   ├── hub.go               # Central dispatcher, room management\n│   │   ├── client.go            # Single WebSocket connection handler\n│   │   └── handler.go           # WS upgrade endpoint\n│   ├── ingest/\n│   │   ├── rtmp.go              # RTMP server, accepts streams\n│   │   └── transcoder.go        # FFmpeg process lifecycle\n│   ├── hls/\n│   │   ├── handler.go           # GET /live/{quality}/playlist.m3u8, GET /live/{quality}/{segment}.ts\n│   │   └── store.go             # Segment file management, cleanup\n│   ├── admin/\n│   │   └── handler.go           # Admin-only API: settings, bans, CDN config\n│   └── db/\n│       ├── sqlite.go            # DB connection, initialization\n│       └── migrations.go        # Schema creation & migrations\n├── CLAUDE.md\n├── TODO.md\n├── go.mod\n└── go.sum\n```\n\n## API Endpoints (MVP)\n\n### Auth (no auth required)\n- `POST /api/auth/register` — `{username, password}` → creates user, returns JWT\n- `POST /api/auth/login` — `{username, password}` → validates, returns JWT\n\n### Stream (auth required for some)\n- `GET /live/{quality}/playlist.m3u8` — HLS master/variant playlist (public)\n- `GET /live/{quality}/{segment}.ts` — HLS segment file (public)\n- `GET /api/stream/status` — current stream info (public)\n\n### Chat (auth required)\n- `WS /ws/chat` — WebSocket connection, JWT in query param or first message\n\n### Admin (admin auth required)\n- `GET /api/admin/settings` — get server settings\n- `PUT /api/admin/settings` — update server settings\n- `GET /api/admin/users` — list users\n- `POST /api/admin/ban` — ban a user\n- `DELETE /api/admin/ban/{userId}` — unban\n\n## Development Commands\n\n```bash\n# Run the server\ngo run ./cmd/server\n\n# Build single binary\ngo build -o desent-server ./cmd/server\n\n# Run tests\ngo test ./...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./...\n```\n\n## MVP Scope\n\nBuilding the **streamer server only** (single binary). Mocked auth with login/password (real users in SQLite, but no email verification, no OAuth — just username+password→JWT).\n\n### In Scope\n- RTMP ingest + FFmpeg transcoding to HLS\n- HLS segment serving (multi-quality)\n- WebSocket chat with broadcast\n- Auth: register/login with username+password, JWT tokens\n- Admin API (REST, no UI)\n- SQLite storage\n\n### Out of Scope (future)\n- Discovery service (cloud catalog)\n- Edge CDN nodes\n- Admin React SPA\n- OAuth / social login\n- Installer/deployment scripts\n- Content moderation system\n\n## Conventions\n\n- Use Go stdlib where possible (`net/http`, `log/slog`, `encoding/json`)\n- Structured logging with `log/slog`\n- Errors: wrap with `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`\n- No frameworks — keep dependencies minimal\n- Tests alongside code (`*_test.go` in same package)\n- Context propagation through all handlers\n- Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n",
