tion\n│   │   ├── middleware.go           — RequireAuth, RequireAdmin, ClaimsFromContext\n│   │   └── handler.go             — POST /api/auth/register, POST /api/auth/login\n│   ├── ingest/\n│   │   ├── ffmpeg.go               — FFmpeg arg builder (multi-quality HLS command)\n│   │   └── manager.go             — subprocess lifecycle (start/restart/stop loop)\n│   └── hls/\n│       ├── handler.go              — serve .m3u8/.ts with MIME types, CORS, cache headers\n│       └── cleaner.go             — background goroutine to remove orphan segments\n├── static/player.html              — minimal hls.js test page\n├── go.mod\n└── go.sum\n```\n\nRoot `main.go` (GoLand placeholder) will be deleted.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: Foundation\n\n**Files:** `go.mod` (edit), `internal/config/config.go`, `internal/db/sqlite.go`, `internal/db/migrations.go`, `cmd/server/main.go` (initial version with /health only)\n\n- Set `go 1.23` in go.mod, `go get` all three dependencies\n- Config: load from env vars with defaults (`HTTP_ADDR=:8080`, `DB_PATH=./desent.db`, `JWT_SECRET` required, `STREAM_KEY=live`, `HLS_DIR=/tmp/hls`, `RTMP_ADDR=0.0.0.0:1935`, `FFMPEG_PATH=ffmpeg`)\n- SQLite: open with WAL mode, write pool (1 conn), read pool (4 conns)\n- Migrations: `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (id, username UNIQUE, password_hash, role DEFAULT 'viewer', created_at)` and `settings (key PRIMARY, value)`\n- Main: load config → open DB → migrate → HTTP server with graceful shutdown (signal.NotifyContext for SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n- Delete root `main.go`\n\n**Test:** `JWT_SECRET=dev go run ./cmd/server` → `curl localhost:8080/health` → `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`\n\n### Step 2: Auth\n\n**Files:** `internal/auth/store.go`, `internal/auth/jwt.go`, `internal/auth/middleware.go`, `internal/auth/handler.go`, update `cmd/server/main.go`\n\n- Store: `CreateUser` (bcrypt hash, first user gets `admin` role), `GetByUsername`\n- JWT: `TokenService` with `Generate(user)` → signed HS256 token (24h expiry),