ine, register HLS routes, start cleaner\n\n**Test:**\n1. Start server: `JWT_SECRET=dev go run ./cmd/server`\n2. OBS → Settings → Stream → Custom → Server: `rtmp://localhost:1935/live/` → Key: `live`\n3. Start streaming in OBS\n4. `curl localhost:8080/api/stream/status` → `{\"live\":true,...}`\n5. `curl localhost:8080/live/master.m3u8` → HLS master playlist\n6. Open `localhost:8080/static/player.html` in browser → live video\n\n## Verification\n\nAfter all 3 steps, the full flow works:\n1. Register a user → get JWT\n2. Start OBS stream → FFmpeg transcodes to 3 qualities\n3. Browser loads hls.js player → fetches master.m3u8 → auto-selects quality → plays live video\n4. Stop OBS → FFmpeg exits → manager restarts FFmpeg (waits for next stream)\n5. Ctrl+C server → graceful shutdown (FFmpeg killed, DB closed)\n"
