tion\n│   │   ├── middleware.go           — RequireAuth, RequireAdmin, ClaimsFromContext\n│   │   └── handler.go             — POST /api/auth/register, POST /api/auth/login\n│   ├── ingest/\n│   │   ├── ffmpeg.go               — FFmpeg arg builder (multi-quality HLS command)\n│   │   └── manager.go             — subprocess lifecycle (start/restart/stop loop)\n│   └── hls/\n│       ├── handler.go              — serve .m3u8/.ts with MIME types, CORS, cache headers\n│       └── cleaner.go             — background goroutine to remove orphan segments\n├── static/player.html              — minimal hls.js test page\n├── Dockerfile                      — multi-stage build: Go binary + FFmpeg\n├── docker-compose.yml              — single command to run everything\n├── go.mod\n└── go.sum\n```\n\nRoot `main.go` (GoLand placeholder) will be deleted.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: Foundation\n\n**Files:** `go.mod` (edit), `internal/config/config.go`, `internal/db/sqlite.go`, `internal/db/migrations.go`, `cmd/server/main.go` (initial version with /health only)\n\n- Set `go 1.23` in go.mod, `go get` all three dependencies\n- Config: load from env vars with defaults (`HTTP_ADDR=:8080`, `DB_PATH=./desent.db`, `JWT_SECRET` required, `STREAM_KEY=live`, `HLS_DIR=/tmp/hls`, `RTMP_ADDR=0.0.0.0:1935`, `FFMPEG_PATH=ffmpeg`)\n- SQLite: open with WAL mode, write pool (1 conn), read pool (4 conns)\n- Migrations: `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (id, username UNIQUE, password_hash, role DEFAULT 'viewer', created_at)` and `settings (key PRIMARY, value)`\n- Main: load config → open DB → migrate → HTTP server with graceful shutdown (signal.NotifyContext for SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n- Delete root `main.go`\n\n**Test:** `JWT_SECRET=dev go run ./cmd/server` → `curl localhost:8080/health` → `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`\n\n### Step 2: Auth\n\n**Files:** `internal/auth/store.go`, `internal/auth/jwt.go`, `internal/auth/middleware.go`, `internal/auth/handler.go`, update `cmd/server/main.go`\n\n- Store: `CreateUser` (bcrypt hash, first user gets `admin` role), `GetByUsername`\n- JWT: `TokenService` with `Generate(user)` → signed HS256 token (24h expiry), `Validate(tokenStr)` → Claims (with alg pinning to prevent alg:none attack)\n- Middleware: `RequireAuth` extracts Bearer token → validates → injects Claims into context. `RequireAdmin` checks role.\n- Handlers: `POST /api/auth/register` (username 3-32 chars, password 8+ chars → create user → return JWT), `POST /api/auth/login` (verify credentials → return JWT). Same error message for \"user not found\" and \"wrong password\" (prevents enumeration).\n- Wire into main.go: create store + token service + handler, register routes\n\n**Test:**\n```\ncurl -X POST localhost:8080/api/auth/register -d '{\"username\":\"alice\",\"password\":\"password123\"}'\n→ {\"token\":\"eyJ...\",\"role\":\"admin\"}\n\ncurl -X POST localhost:8080/api/auth/login -d '{\"username\":\"alice\",\"password\":\"password123\"}'\n→ {\"token\":\"eyJ...\",\"role\":\"admin\"}\n```\n\n### Step 3: RTMP Ingest + HLS Delivery\n\n**Files:** `internal/ingest/ffmpeg.go`, `internal/ingest/manager.go`, `internal/hls/handler.go`, `internal/hls/cleaner.go`, `static/player.html`, update `cmd/server/main.go`\n\n- FFmpeg args builder: input `rtmp://0.0.0.0:1935/live/STREAM_KEY` with `-listen 1`, output 3 quality variants (720p/480p/360p) as HLS segments (2s, list size 5, `delete_segments+independent_segments`), master playlist\n- Manager: goroutine loop — start FFmpeg, wait for exit, restart after 2s pause. `IsLive()` atomic flag. Clean stop via context cancellation + SIGTERM to FFmpeg process.\n- HLS handler: `http.FileServer` under `GET /live/` with MIME types (`.m3u8` → `application/vnd.apple.mpegurl`, `.ts` → `video/mp2t`), Cache-Control (`no-cache` for playlists, `max-age=3600` for segments), CORS headers\n- Stream status: `GET /api/stream/status` → `{\"live\":true/false,\"qualities\":[\"720p\",\"480p\",\"360p\"]}`\n- Cleaner: every 30s, remove `.ts` files older than 60s (handles orphans after FFmpeg crash)\n- Test player: minimal HTML with hls.js from CDN\n- Main.go: create HLS dirs, start ingest manager goroutine, register HLS routes, start cleaner\n\n**Test:**\n1. Start server: `JWT_SECRET=dev go run ./cmd/server`\n2. OBS → Settings → Stream → Custom → Server: `rtmp://localhost:1935/live/` → Key: `live`\n3. Start streaming in OBS\n4. `curl localhost:8080/api/stream/status` → `{\"live\":true,...}`\n5. `curl localhost:8080/live/master.m3u8` → HLS master playlist\n6. Open `localhost:8080/static/player.html` in browser → live video\n\n### Step 4: Docker\n\n**Files:** `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `.dockerignore`\n\n- **Dockerfile** (multi-stage):\n  - Stage 1 (`builder`): `golang:1.23-alpine`, copy source, `go build -o /server ./cmd/server`\n  - Stage 2 (`runtime`): `alpine:3.19`, install `ffmpeg` from apk, copy Go binary + static files from builder\n  - Exposes ports 8080 (HTTP) and 1935 (RTMP)\n  - Entrypoint: `/server`\n\n- **docker-compose.yml**:\n  ```yaml\n  services:\n    server:\n      build: .\n      ports:\n        - \"8080:8080\"   # HTTP (HLS + API)\n        - \"1935:1935\"   # RTMP (OBS ingest)\n      environment:\n        - JWT_SECRET=dev-secret-change-me\n        - STREAM_KEY=live\n        - DB_PATH=/data/desent.db\n        - HLS_DIR=/tmp/hls\n      volumes:\n        - db-data:/data          # persist SQLite across restarts\n      restart: unless-stopped\n  volumes:\n    db-data:\n  ```\n\n- **.dockerignore**: `.git`, `.idea`, `*.db`, `/tmp`\n\n**Test:**\n```bash\ndocker compose up --build\n# OBS → rtmp://localhost:1935/live/ → Key: live\n# Browser → http://localhost:8080/static/player.html\n# curl http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register -d '{\"username\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"password123\"}'\n```\n\n## Verification\n\nEnd-to-end test via Docker:\n1. `docker compose up --build` — builds Go binary + FFmpeg container, starts server\n2. `curl localhost:8080/health` → `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`\n3. Register: `curl -X POST localhost:8080/api/auth/register -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"password123\"}'` → JWT + admin role\n4. OBS → Custom server `rtmp://localhost:1935/live/` → Key: `live` → Start Streaming\n5. `curl localhost:8080/api/stream/status` → `{\"live\":true,...}`\n6. `curl localhost:8080/live/master.m3u8` → HLS master playlist with 3 variants\n7. Open `http://localhost:8080/static/player.html` in browser → live video plays\n8. Stop OBS → FFmpeg exits → manager restarts (waiting for next stream)\n9. `docker compose down` → clean shutdown\n"
